WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:18.585
It's happening!

3
00:03:22.755 --> 00:03:24.382
Wait up. guys!

4
00:03:32.765 --> 00:03:34.225
The baby's coming! The baby's coming!

5
00:03:34.350 --> 00:03:35.810
- Watch it!
- I'm having a baby!

6
00:03:35.935 --> 00:03:39.314
- Code Blue! Code Blue!
- Or pink if it's a girl!

7
00:03:39.439 --> 00:03:42.567
Having a baby! Having a baby!
I'm coming. Ellie!

8
00:03:42.984 --> 00:03:44.319
We got it!

9
00:03:58.374 --> 00:03:59.918
Ellie! Ellie!

10
00:04:00.043 --> 00:04:03.087
Ellie. where are you? Where am I?

11
00:04:03.212 --> 00:04:04.339
Manny?

12
00:04:05.381 --> 00:04:07.675
I told you it was just a kick.

13
00:04:10.803 --> 00:04:13.764
Right! Right! Wow.

14
00:04:14.932 --> 00:04:19.228
You really gave Daddy a scare!
Daddy got silly!

15
00:04:19.353 --> 00:04:22.606
Daddy fall down cliff
and go boom. boom. boom.

16
00:04:22.731 --> 00:04:25.525
Silly Daddy. Yeah.

17
00:04:29.863 --> 00:04:33.283
Sorry. folks! False alarm!
It was just a kick!

18
00:04:34.826 --> 00:04:38.288
- You know who I'd like to kick?
- That's the third false alarm this week.

19
00:04:38.413 --> 00:04:41.667
All right. show's over. break it up!
Break it up!

20
00:04:42.417 --> 00:04:45.337
I see someone else
who has a bun in the oven!

21
00:04:45.837 --> 00:04:47.589
I'm not pregnant!

22
00:04:48.757 --> 00:04:51.718
That's too bad.
You'd make a wonderful mother!

23
00:04:52.886 --> 00:04:57.808
Manny. I know you're excited. I am. too.
But you're getting a little carried away.

24
00:04:57.933 --> 00:05:02.688
Okay. okay!
Boy. you're starting to sound like Diego.

25
00:05:03.730 --> 00:05:06.024
Wait a second. Where is Diego?

26
00:06:01.704 --> 00:06:04.832
My hooves are burning. baby!
They are burning!

27
00:06:05.750 --> 00:06:07.710
Look at this. I got to tip-toe!
I got to tip-toe!

28
00:06:07.835 --> 00:06:09.587
Eat my dust. dingo!

29
00:06:13.007 --> 00:06:15.468
Now? Can I look now?

30
00:06:15.843 --> 00:06:18.387
Easy. Don't freak out the baby.

31
00:06:18.512 --> 00:06:22.266
The baby's fine. It's the freaked-out daddy
I'm worried about.

32
00:06:22.642 --> 00:06:24.227
No peeking!

33
00:06:25.478 --> 00:06:28.064
Voil�! Playground for Junior!

34
00:06:29.815 --> 00:06:30.858
Wow.

35
00:06:38.491 --> 00:06:40.952
It's amazing!

36
00:06:52.296 --> 00:06:53.548
Manny.

37
00:06:53.673 --> 00:06:56.425
I made it myself. Our family.

38
00:07:02.974 --> 00:07:04.684
Hey. why aren't I up there?

39
00:07:04.809 --> 00:07:08.354
- You can be on ours.
- You'd fit right in!

40
00:07:09.063 --> 00:07:10.439
Thanks!

41
00:07:10.565 --> 00:07:15.361
Of course. it's still a work in progress.
A few rough edges here and there.

42
00:07:16.279 --> 00:07:19.490
I don't believe it.
You're trying to baby-proof nature.

43
00:07:19.615 --> 00:07:23.369
Baby-proof nature? Get out of here.
That's ridiculous.

44
00:07:26.497 --> 00:07:29.458
Manny. this is the world our baby's
gonna grow up in.

45
00:07:29.584 --> 00:07:30.751
You can't change that.

46
00:07:30.876 --> 00:07:34.130
Of course I can.
I'm the biggest thing on Earth!

47
00:07:34.255 --> 00:07:38.718
Okay. Big Daddy. I can't wait to see
how you handle the teen years.

48
00:07:41.929 --> 00:07:44.974
Come on. Sid!
I don't want you touching anything.

49
00:07:45.099 --> 00:07:47.977
This place is for kids. Are you a kid?

50
00:07:48.561 --> 00:07:50.353
Don't answer that.

51
00:08:02.616 --> 00:08:04.326
Diego! There you are.

52
00:08:04.451 --> 00:08:05.869
You missed the big surprise!

53
00:08:05.994 --> 00:08:08.872
Right. Right. I'll check it out later.

54
00:08:08.997 --> 00:08:10.540
Okay. See you.

55
00:08:11.458 --> 00:08:14.002
You know. I think there's
something bothering Diego.

56
00:08:14.127 --> 00:08:16.004
No. I'm sure everything's fine.

57
00:08:16.129 --> 00:08:17.214
You should talk to him.

58
00:08:17.339 --> 00:08:20.008
Guys don't talk to guys
about guy problems.

59
00:08:20.133 --> 00:08:22.969
We just punch each other
on the shoulders.

60
00:08:23.678 --> 00:08:25.013
That's stupid.

61
00:08:25.138 --> 00:08:29.184
To a girl. To a guy.
that's like six months of therapy.

62
00:08:30.769 --> 00:08:32.896
Okay. okay. I'm going.

63
00:08:37.108 --> 00:08:38.193
Hey.

64
00:08:41.905 --> 00:08:43.531
Why'd you do that?

65
00:08:43.990 --> 00:08:45.450
I don't know.

66
00:08:47.369 --> 00:08:48.787
So. listen.

67
00:08:49.412 --> 00:08:53.124
Ellie thinks there's
something bothering you. I told her...

68
00:08:53.250 --> 00:08:55.919
Actually. I've been thinking that soon

69
00:08:56.044 --> 00:08:58.713
it might be time for me to head out.

70
00:08:59.589 --> 00:09:03.385
Okay. So I'll just tell her that you're fine.
It was nothing.

71
00:09:03.510 --> 00:09:06.972
Look. who are we kidding. Manny?
I'm losing my edge.

72
00:09:07.097 --> 00:09:09.933
I'm not really built
for chaperoning play dates.

73
00:09:10.058 --> 00:09:11.393
What are you talking about?

74
00:09:11.518 --> 00:09:14.646
Having a family. that's huge.
and I'm happy for you.

75
00:09:14.771 --> 00:09:17.649
but that's your adventure. not mine.

76
00:09:18.441 --> 00:09:21.236
- So you don't want to be around my kid?
- No. no. no. That's...

77
00:09:21.361 --> 00:09:23.321
- You're taking this the wrong way.
- No. go.

78
00:09:23.446 --> 00:09:27.158
Go find some adventure.
Mr. Adventure Guy.

79
00:09:27.284 --> 00:09:31.788
Don't let my boring domestic life
hit you in the butt on the way out.

80
00:09:31.913 --> 00:09:35.750
Isn't Ellie supposed to be the one
with the hormonal imbalance?

81
00:09:35.875 --> 00:09:38.377
Manny. wait! No one has to leave.

82
00:09:39.962 --> 00:09:43.173
- So?
- That's why guys don't talk to guys.

83
00:09:43.299 --> 00:09:46.427
- Why? What happened?
- Diego's leaving.

84
00:09:50.306 --> 00:09:54.184
This should be the best time of our lives.
We're having a baby!

85
00:09:54.310 --> 00:09:56.645
No. Sid. They're having a baby.

86
00:09:57.646 --> 00:10:00.608
Yeah. but we're a herd. a family.

87
00:10:01.817 --> 00:10:05.446
Look. things have changed.
Manny has other priorities now.

88
00:10:06.488 --> 00:10:11.076
Face it. Sid. We had a great run.
but now it's time to move on.

89
00:10:12.620 --> 00:10:14.788
So it's just the two of us.

90
00:10:15.164 --> 00:10:17.625
No. Sid. it's not the two of us.

91
00:10:18.584 --> 00:10:21.128
Crash and Eddie are coming with us?

92
00:10:22.171 --> 00:10:23.631
Just Crash?

93
00:10:25.174 --> 00:10:26.592
Just Eddie?

94
00:10:28.677 --> 00:10:30.012
Bye. Sid.

95
00:10:42.191 --> 00:10:45.110
Okay. calm down. Calm down.

96
00:10:45.236 --> 00:10:49.740
I'm good at making friends.
I'll make my own herd. That's what I'll do.

97
00:10:49.865 --> 00:10:52.326
Patty cake. patty cake. baker's man...

98
00:11:02.670 --> 00:11:05.464
Well. at least you still got your looks.

99
00:11:16.850 --> 00:11:17.893
Great.

100
00:11:25.776 --> 00:11:28.861
Anybody here? Anyone?

101
00:11:49.048 --> 00:11:50.383
Hello?

102
00:11:57.724 --> 00:12:01.352
Poor guys. I know what it's like
to feel abandoned.

103
00:12:07.859 --> 00:12:10.737
Don't worry. You're not alone anymore.

104
00:12:43.478 --> 00:12:44.938
There you go.

105
00:12:51.444 --> 00:12:53.821
Okay. okay. I'm okay. I'm okay.

106
00:12:59.160 --> 00:13:01.955
Stay here. Stay here. And you.
you take care of your brother. now.

107
00:13:02.080 --> 00:13:03.623
Momma's gonna be right back.

108
00:13:03.748 --> 00:13:05.541
Momma's coming. baby!

109
00:13:12.674 --> 00:13:13.967
Gotcha!

110
00:13:17.344 --> 00:13:19.596
What did I just tell you kids?

111
00:14:26.705 --> 00:14:28.999
Thank you. thank you. thank you!

112
00:14:29.541 --> 00:14:31.126
Bad egg. Rotten egg!

113
00:14:31.251 --> 00:14:33.754
A heart attack you almost gave me!

114
00:14:34.087 --> 00:14:37.341
I'm sorry. darling.
It's just that I love you so much.

115
00:14:37.466 --> 00:14:40.552
Now. I want you to meet
your Uncle Manny and your Aunt Ellie.

116
00:14:40.677 --> 00:14:43.055
- Hi!
- Hello.

117
00:14:43.430 --> 00:14:47.226
I'd like to present Egbert. Shelly and Yoko.

118
00:14:47.643 --> 00:14:51.063
Sid. whatever you're doing. it's a bad idea.

119
00:14:51.980 --> 00:14:53.482
My kids will hear you!

120
00:14:53.607 --> 00:14:56.693
They're not your kids. Sid.
Take them back.

121
00:14:56.818 --> 00:14:59.238
- You're not meant to be a parent.
- Why not?

122
00:14:59.363 --> 00:15:01.865
First sign. stealing someone else's eggs.

123
00:15:01.990 --> 00:15:05.117
Second sign. one of them
almost became an omelet.

124
00:15:06.202 --> 00:15:09.038
Sid. someone's probably
worried sick looking for them.

125
00:15:09.163 --> 00:15:11.582
No. They were underground. in ice.

126
00:15:11.707 --> 00:15:15.419
If it wasn't for me. they'd be Eggsicles.

127
00:15:17.296 --> 00:15:19.549
Sid. I know what you're going through.

128
00:15:19.674 --> 00:15:21.926
You're gonna have a family. too. someday.

129
00:15:22.051 --> 00:15:25.638
You're gonna meet a nice girl
with low standards.

130
00:15:25.763 --> 00:15:28.891
no real options or sense of smell...

131
00:15:29.016 --> 00:15:30.351
What Manny means to say is...

132
00:15:30.476 --> 00:15:32.937
No. I get it. I'll take them back.

133
00:15:33.771 --> 00:15:38.025
You have your family.
and I'm better off alone. by myself.

134
00:15:39.819 --> 00:15:41.737
A fortress of solitude.

135
00:15:43.155 --> 00:15:44.782
In the ice

136
00:15:45.658 --> 00:15:47.076
forever!

137
00:15:47.785 --> 00:15:49.996
A lone. lonely loner!

138
00:15:50.997 --> 00:15:53.708
- That's a lot of aloneness.
- Precisely!

139
00:15:54.500 --> 00:15:58.629
- Sid. wait!
- No! No. it's okay. He'll bounce back.

140
00:15:59.005 --> 00:16:01.841
It's one of the advantages of being Sid.

141
00:16:11.350 --> 00:16:15.771
Why should I take you back? I love kids!

142
00:16:15.897 --> 00:16:19.108
I'm responsible. loving. nurturing.

143
00:16:20.401 --> 00:16:22.111
What do you think?

144
00:16:23.863 --> 00:16:25.823
I knew you would agree.

145
00:16:28.576 --> 00:16:31.954
Don't cry! Don't cry.

146
00:16:32.079 --> 00:16:33.748
I'll find a dry place.

147
00:16:37.710 --> 00:16:38.753
Okay.

148
00:16:40.087 --> 00:16:42.131
Here. let me just dry you off.

149
00:16:47.053 --> 00:16:50.097
I don't know.
Being a parent's a lot of work.

150
00:16:51.182 --> 00:16:53.017
Maybe I'm not ready.

151
00:18:30.780 --> 00:18:31.907
Momma!

152
00:18:32.032 --> 00:18:34.576
Momma! Momma! Momma!

153
00:18:38.288 --> 00:18:39.706
I'm a mommy.

154
00:18:42.250 --> 00:18:43.918
Where's Mommy?

155
00:18:46.170 --> 00:18:47.630
Here I am.

156
00:18:50.507 --> 00:18:52.968
There you go. Nice squeaky faces.

157
00:19:09.526 --> 00:19:11.320
I got it! I got it!

158
00:19:16.325 --> 00:19:19.495
No. no! Stop! Not me! No. stop. stop!

159
00:19:21.872 --> 00:19:23.457
Hey! No biting!

160
00:19:27.211 --> 00:19:30.923
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
No. It's okay. it's okay. Don't cry.

161
00:19:31.048 --> 00:19:33.759
Why are you still crying? Are you hungry?

162
00:19:33.884 --> 00:19:36.887
Maybe you're hungry.
I know just the thing.

163
00:19:39.348 --> 00:19:43.686
Hush. hush
You mean. vicious animal

164
00:19:44.186 --> 00:19:48.857
I'm your baby and this is my milk

165
00:19:52.069 --> 00:19:54.530
I thought you were a female!

166
00:21:20.156 --> 00:21:24.661
I'm sorry. but you can't go in.
Manny says it's just for kids.

167
00:21:26.037 --> 00:21:28.248
Wait a minute. You are kids!

168
00:21:31.543 --> 00:21:33.753
Just don't break anything!

169
00:21:34.837 --> 00:21:37.465
The sloth says the playground's open!

170
00:21:38.883 --> 00:21:41.135
No. wait! Not for everyone!

171
00:21:46.266 --> 00:21:48.560
No. no. no! Don't touch that!

172
00:21:54.691 --> 00:21:57.819
- What are they?
- Who cares? They're fun!

173
00:21:57.944 --> 00:22:00.655
- Play nice!
- Mommy. he's not sharing!

174
00:22:00.780 --> 00:22:03.825
- Aren't you going to do something?
- Why? My kid had it first.

175
00:22:03.950 --> 00:22:05.285
- Did not!
- Did. too!

176
00:22:05.410 --> 00:22:06.744
- Did not!
- Did. too!

177
00:22:06.870 --> 00:22:09.664
- Did not!
- Liar. liar. fur on fire!

178
00:22:09.789 --> 00:22:11.332
What is the matter with you?

179
00:22:11.457 --> 00:22:15.670
I'm a single mother with three kids.
I could use a little compassion!

180
00:22:16.713 --> 00:22:18.256
Slow down! No!

181
00:22:18.381 --> 00:22:19.757
No. don't...

182
00:22:20.173 --> 00:22:21.800
Stop. stop. stop!

183
00:22:23.635 --> 00:22:26.096
- Ronald!
- That's a shame.

184
00:22:31.059 --> 00:22:33.186
Stop! Stop. stop. stop!

185
00:22:34.062 --> 00:22:35.355
No! No!

186
00:22:37.566 --> 00:22:40.777
- Hold on. Little Johnny!
- I'm trying!

187
00:22:44.573 --> 00:22:48.493
You know. experts say you should
let the kids eat whatever they want!

188
00:22:49.369 --> 00:22:51.163
Do you think my ankles look fat?

189
00:22:51.288 --> 00:22:53.081
Ankles? What ankles?

190
00:22:57.586 --> 00:22:59.922
Ronald! Where did you come from?

191
00:23:02.341 --> 00:23:03.800
Oh. no.

192
00:23:05.302 --> 00:23:07.429
Okay. come on. Spit him out.

193
00:23:07.971 --> 00:23:09.431
If you don't spit out Little Johnny.

194
00:23:09.556 --> 00:23:11.850
we're leaving the playground this instant!

195
00:23:11.975 --> 00:23:13.143
One.

196
00:23:13.644 --> 00:23:14.937
two...

197
00:23:15.520 --> 00:23:17.814
Don't make me say "three"!

198
00:23:19.399 --> 00:23:22.069
There we are. A picture of health.

199
00:23:22.194 --> 00:23:24.655
- That's not Little Johnny.
- Well. better than nothing.

200
00:23:25.280 --> 00:23:26.740
Madison!

201
00:23:27.449 --> 00:23:30.077
- Come on. barf him up.
- Sid?

202
00:23:30.786 --> 00:23:32.871
Hey. Hey. Manny.

203
00:23:33.830 --> 00:23:35.457
Little Johnny!

204
00:23:39.294 --> 00:23:40.921
Wait! No. no...

205
00:23:43.674 --> 00:23:45.467
I'm really sorry.

206
00:23:51.974 --> 00:23:55.435
- This place is totaled.
- And we didn't wreck it.

207
00:23:55.561 --> 00:23:56.603
We're losing our touch. bro.

208
00:23:56.603 --> 00:23:57.646
We're losing our touch. bro.

209
00:23:58.814 --> 00:24:01.441
Well. the important thing is
that no one got hurt.

210
00:24:02.234 --> 00:24:03.527
Except for that guy.

211
00:24:03.819 --> 00:24:04.945
And those three.

212
00:24:06.196 --> 00:24:07.239
And her.

213
00:24:09.907 --> 00:24:13.160
I told you to take them back.
and you kept them!

214
00:24:13.286 --> 00:24:14.370
Now look what they've done!

215
00:24:14.495 --> 00:24:16.914
Okay. granted.
we do have some discipline issues.

216
00:24:17.039 --> 00:24:19.208
Eating kids is not a discipline issue!

217
00:24:19.333 --> 00:24:21.961
- But he spit them out.
- Well. that's super.

218
00:24:22.086 --> 00:24:24.964
Let's give him a gold star! Kid of the week!

219
00:24:25.423 --> 00:24:26.966
They don't belong here. Sid.

220
00:24:27.091 --> 00:24:30.928
Whatever they are.
wherever you found them. take them back.

221
00:24:31.053 --> 00:24:33.639
Manny! I'm not getting rid of my kids!

222
00:24:35.850 --> 00:24:37.476
Earthquake!

223
00:24:39.353 --> 00:24:42.148
It's okay. it's okay. Momma's here.

224
00:24:44.692 --> 00:24:46.527
Do earthquakes shriek?

225
00:25:15.139 --> 00:25:16.849
I thought those guys were extinct!

226
00:25:16.974 --> 00:25:20.519
Well. then that is one angry fossil. Sid!

227
00:25:21.854 --> 00:25:24.190
Come on. come on! Inside. inside. inside!

228
00:25:41.123 --> 00:25:44.043
Nobody move a muscle.

229
00:26:15.198 --> 00:26:17.993
No. no. no. don't cry. Don't cry.

230
00:26:20.787 --> 00:26:24.416
We are poor. little lambs
who have lost our way

231
00:26:37.637 --> 00:26:41.433
Sid! Give them to her! She's their mother!

232
00:26:41.558 --> 00:26:43.393
How do I know she's their mother?

233
00:26:43.518 --> 00:26:46.938
What do you want. a birth certificate?
She's a dinosaur!

234
00:26:47.063 --> 00:26:50.817
Well. I put in the blood. sweat and tears
to raise them!

235
00:26:50.942 --> 00:26:53.778
For a day! Give them back. you lunatic!

236
00:26:53.904 --> 00:26:56.198
Look. these are my kids.

237
00:26:57.199 --> 00:27:00.535
and you're gonna have to go through me
to get them!

238
00:27:06.082 --> 00:27:07.375
- Sid!
- Sid!

239
00:27:08.835 --> 00:27:10.128
Help!

240
00:27:16.509 --> 00:27:17.969
Run!

241
00:27:18.261 --> 00:27:20.555
Don't you have anything better to do?

242
00:27:25.143 --> 00:27:26.311
Sid?

243
00:27:42.494 --> 00:27:44.454
Sid must be down there.

244
00:27:44.871 --> 00:27:47.248
- Well. he's dead.
- Real shame.

245
00:27:47.373 --> 00:27:49.041
He will be missed.

246
00:27:49.625 --> 00:27:52.169
Oh. no. no. no. Not so fast.

247
00:27:52.294 --> 00:27:54.838
Okay. Ellie. this is where I draw the line.

248
00:27:54.964 --> 00:27:57.466
You. Crash and Eddie. back to the village.

249
00:27:57.591 --> 00:27:59.176
Yeah. that's gonna happen.

250
00:27:59.301 --> 00:28:03.138
Ellie. you saw that thing!
This is gonna be dangerous!

251
00:28:03.264 --> 00:28:04.598
Talk to the trunk.

252
00:28:04.723 --> 00:28:08.060
Great. After we save Sid.
I'm gonna kill him.

253
00:28:10.062 --> 00:28:12.231
- Ladies first.
- Age before beauty.

254
00:28:12.356 --> 00:28:14.525
- No pain. no gain.
- What pain?

255
00:28:25.536 --> 00:28:28.289
- Sid!
- Sid!

256
00:28:39.216 --> 00:28:43.220
Oh. no. No. no. Not good. not good.

257
00:28:45.389 --> 00:28:47.516
Ellie! Ellie. wait up!

258
00:28:50.769 --> 00:28:53.272
Okay. look. if you feel anything.

259
00:28:53.397 --> 00:28:56.775
even if it's nothing. you gotta tell me.
and then we're out of here.

260
00:28:56.901 --> 00:28:58.027
Okay.

261
00:28:58.485 --> 00:28:59.904
We need a code word!

262
00:29:00.029 --> 00:29:03.157
Yeah. Something that says.
"The baby's coming."

263
00:29:04.074 --> 00:29:07.870
How about. "The baby's coming!"
How's that?

264
00:29:08.621 --> 00:29:12.583
Too long. We need something
short and punchy. like...

265
00:29:12.708 --> 00:29:13.792
"Peaches!"

266
00:29:13.918 --> 00:29:16.253
- Peaches?
- I love peaches.

267
00:29:16.378 --> 00:29:20.424
They're sweet and round and fuzzy.
just like you.

268
00:29:20.549 --> 00:29:22.259
You think I'm round?

269
00:29:23.510 --> 00:29:26.722
Round is good. Round is foxy.

270
00:29:38.316 --> 00:29:39.651
Stay close.

271
00:30:00.880 --> 00:30:03.216
Are you guys
having the same dream I am?

272
00:30:03.341 --> 00:30:07.762
We've been living above an entire world.
and we didn't even know it.

273
00:30:31.286 --> 00:30:34.122
Run for it! Hurry!

274
00:30:41.087 --> 00:30:44.632
- Diego. what are you doing here?
- Sightseeing!

275
00:30:44.757 --> 00:30:48.011
- I'm looking for Sid. same as you.
- Well! Aren't you noble?

276
00:30:48.136 --> 00:30:52.015
This is not the time. guys!
We need all the help we can get!

277
00:31:02.817 --> 00:31:04.235
Never mind.

278
00:31:14.287 --> 00:31:17.749
Here. boy! Here! Come on!
Good boy! Come on!

279
00:31:18.458 --> 00:31:20.335
- Climb on.
- Are you nuts?

280
00:31:20.460 --> 00:31:21.669
We're not getting on that thing!

281
00:31:21.794 --> 00:31:24.422
It's either this dinosaur or that one!

282
00:31:27.633 --> 00:31:31.094
Pregnant lady wants to live!
Yabba-dabba-doo!

283
00:31:42.814 --> 00:31:45.817
Don't ever yabba-dabba do that again!

284
00:31:51.573 --> 00:31:56.161
- I feel so puny.
- How do you think I feel?

285
00:32:19.768 --> 00:32:21.311
Take cover!

286
00:33:09.818 --> 00:33:12.988
Dude. you're awesome!
You're like the brother I never had!

287
00:33:13.113 --> 00:33:14.447
Me. too!

288
00:33:27.335 --> 00:33:28.878
Can we keep him?

289
00:33:31.631 --> 00:33:33.090
- Buck!
- What?

290
00:33:33.341 --> 00:33:36.052
The name's Buck. Short for Buckminster.

291
00:33:37.261 --> 00:33:39.555
Long for "Buh."

292
00:33:41.933 --> 00:33:43.476
A little dull.

293
00:33:45.269 --> 00:33:46.938
What are you doing here?

294
00:33:47.063 --> 00:33:49.607
- Our friend was taken by a dinosaur.
- Well!

295
00:33:50.358 --> 00:33:54.403
He's dead. Welcome to my world.
Now go home.

296
00:33:54.737 --> 00:33:56.697
- Off you pop.
- Not without Sid.

297
00:33:56.822 --> 00:34:00.201
Ellie. wait.
Maybe the deranged hermit has a point.

298
00:34:00.326 --> 00:34:02.912
Manny. we came this far.
we're gonna find him.

299
00:34:03.037 --> 00:34:04.580
I got tracks.

300
00:34:06.999 --> 00:34:08.292
Let's go.

301
00:34:11.003 --> 00:34:13.214
If you go in there. you'll find your friend.

302
00:34:14.215 --> 00:34:16.008
In the afterlife.

303
00:34:16.509 --> 00:34:19.804
How do you know.
O Great and Wisely Weasely One?

304
00:34:28.104 --> 00:34:29.105
Yeah.

305
00:34:29.230 --> 00:34:34.026
Mommy dinosaur carrying her three babies
and some floppy green thing.

306
00:34:34.986 --> 00:34:37.405
Yeah. we're friends
with the floppy green thing.

307
00:34:37.530 --> 00:34:39.282
You got all that from the tracks?

308
00:34:39.407 --> 00:34:41.909
No. Not really.
I saw them come through here earlier.

309
00:34:42.034 --> 00:34:43.452
She's headed for Lava Falls.

310
00:34:44.912 --> 00:34:47.456
That's where they care for the newborns.

311
00:34:47.582 --> 00:34:51.794
To get there. you've got to go
through the Jungle of Misery.

312
00:34:51.919 --> 00:34:54.422
across the Chasm of Death

313
00:34:56.507 --> 00:34:58.968
to the Plates of Woe.

314
00:35:01.888 --> 00:35:05.932
Okay! Good luck with the slow
descent into madness.

315
00:35:06.057 --> 00:35:07.142
We're gonna go now.

316
00:35:10.937 --> 00:35:13.732
What. you think this is
some sort of tropical getaway?

317
00:35:14.357 --> 00:35:16.985
You can't protect your mate. mate.

318
00:35:17.569 --> 00:35:20.655
What are you gonna do
with those flimsy tusks

319
00:35:20.780 --> 00:35:23.158
when you run into the beast?

320
00:35:24.743 --> 00:35:26.286
I call him

321
00:35:26.786 --> 00:35:28.330
Rudy.

322
00:35:28.455 --> 00:35:32.167
Oh. good. Good. I was worried
it was something intimidating.

323
00:35:32.292 --> 00:35:35.003
like "Sheldon" or "Tim."

324
00:35:35.420 --> 00:35:38.924
Wait. You mean there's something
bigger than Mommy Dinosaur?

325
00:35:39.049 --> 00:35:40.425
- Aye.
- Eye?

326
00:35:40.842 --> 00:35:43.929
Aye. aye! He's the one that gave me this!

327
00:35:45.513 --> 00:35:49.601
- He gave you that patch?
- For free? That's so cool.

328
00:35:49.726 --> 00:35:52.187
Yeah. Maybe he'll give us one. too.

329
00:35:56.483 --> 00:35:58.235
Welcome to my world.

330
00:36:01.863 --> 00:36:04.741
Abandon all hope. he who enters there!

331
00:36:04.866 --> 00:36:06.826
All right! We get it!

332
00:36:06.952 --> 00:36:09.913
Doom and despair. yada. yada. yada.

333
00:37:23.611 --> 00:37:26.197
Sounds like a jungle of misery to me.

334
00:37:40.002 --> 00:37:43.422
- Hold on.
- Why? What's wrong? Peaches?

335
00:37:43.547 --> 00:37:47.801
What? No! It's just I got a funny feeling.

336
00:37:48.135 --> 00:37:51.472
You're hungry! Low blood sugar.
There's some fruit!

337
00:37:52.181 --> 00:37:55.142
- No! Manny!
- I wouldn't do that if I were you.

338
00:37:55.809 --> 00:37:58.437
This isn't exactly your playground.

339
00:37:59.313 --> 00:38:01.899
Like I'm really gonna be afraid
of a pretty flower.

340
00:38:04.485 --> 00:38:06.195
Bet you didn't see that coming.

341
00:38:07.696 --> 00:38:10.658
- Manny!
- For the record. I blame you for this.

342
00:38:13.118 --> 00:38:15.454
Stop eating our friends. plant!

343
00:38:21.168 --> 00:38:23.504
That's it! I'm tearing it up from the roots!

344
00:38:23.629 --> 00:38:27.341
- Do that. and it will clamp shut forever.
- What?

345
00:38:27.466 --> 00:38:30.010
All right. preggers.
don't get your trunk in a knot.

346
00:38:30.135 --> 00:38:31.804
I'll have them out of there
before they're digested.

347
00:38:31.929 --> 00:38:33.180
Digested?

348
00:38:33.847 --> 00:38:35.683
They'll be nothing but bones
in three minutes.

349
00:38:35.808 --> 00:38:37.226
Well. maybe five for the fat one.

350
00:38:37.351 --> 00:38:38.978
I'm not fat!

351
00:38:40.562 --> 00:38:41.855
I feel tingly.

352
00:38:41.980 --> 00:38:44.023
Don't say that
when you're pressed up against me.

353
00:38:44.148 --> 00:38:46.067
Not that kind of tingly.

354
00:38:46.359 --> 00:38:48.194
I can feel it. too.

355
00:38:50.071 --> 00:38:51.990
Help! Someone help us!

356
00:38:52.282 --> 00:38:53.324
Hurry!

357
00:38:53.449 --> 00:38:55.201
It's time to get

358
00:38:55.535 --> 00:38:57.036
Buck Wild.

359
00:39:06.379 --> 00:39:08.006
Who's fat now?

360
00:39:31.696 --> 00:39:32.947
No!

361
00:40:13.655 --> 00:40:14.822
Tourists.

362
00:40:14.948 --> 00:40:16.950
Barfed on by a plant.

363
00:40:17.325 --> 00:40:18.618
- Awesome!
- Awesome!

364
00:40:19.327 --> 00:40:20.954
Say something.

365
00:40:22.497 --> 00:40:24.457
Thanks for saving us.

366
00:40:24.874 --> 00:40:27.794
Buck. will you help us find
the floppy green thing?

367
00:40:27.919 --> 00:40:30.504
- That's not necessary!
- Yes. it is.

368
00:40:32.839 --> 00:40:34.800
All right. I'll help you.

369
00:40:34.925 --> 00:40:36.385
But I got rules.

370
00:40:36.510 --> 00:40:39.763
Rule number one. always listen to Buck.

371
00:40:41.014 --> 00:40:44.268
Rule number two.
stay in the middle of the trail.

372
00:40:44.852 --> 00:40:46.478
Rule number three.

373
00:40:50.691 --> 00:40:53.777
he who has gas
travels at the back of the pack.

374
00:40:56.989 --> 00:40:59.157
Come on. then. Chop. chop!

375
00:40:59.575 --> 00:41:01.785
We should all have our heads examined.

376
00:41:01.910 --> 00:41:05.497
That's rule number four!
Now let's go find your friend!

377
00:41:26.977 --> 00:41:30.856
It's okay. It's okay. Don't worry.
We're gonna be fine.

378
00:41:30.981 --> 00:41:33.734
Please stop swaying. A little nauseous.

379
00:41:38.947 --> 00:41:41.992
See? She's putting us down...

380
00:41:44.578 --> 00:41:48.415
No! I'm too young to be eaten!

381
00:41:51.710 --> 00:41:54.922
Nice mucus.
And I don't say that to everyone.

382
00:42:08.602 --> 00:42:12.231
Listen. families get complicated!
Maybe we can work something out.

383
00:42:12.356 --> 00:42:14.441
I can take them Sunday to Tuesday!

384
00:42:14.566 --> 00:42:17.110
Wednesday to Friday? Weekends?

385
00:42:24.867 --> 00:42:27.620
It's okay! Momma's okay.

386
00:42:30.122 --> 00:42:32.917
If you eat me. it will send a bad message.

387
00:42:38.714 --> 00:42:40.758
Score one for the sloth!

388
00:42:46.055 --> 00:42:48.266
And the score's all tied up.

389
00:42:53.229 --> 00:42:55.273
Do you think the beast will find Sid?

390
00:42:55.398 --> 00:42:57.942
Or more importantly. us?

391
00:42:58.067 --> 00:42:59.986
Rudy? Are you joking?

392
00:43:00.403 --> 00:43:05.032
He's relentless.
He knows all. sees all. eats all.

393
00:43:06.492 --> 00:43:08.119
So that's a yes.

394
00:43:12.623 --> 00:43:15.585
Hey! Get off my lawn! Go on! Shoo!

395
00:43:21.173 --> 00:43:22.717
I knew that guy when he was a caterpillar.

396
00:43:22.842 --> 00:43:24.886
You know. before he came out.

397
00:43:27.096 --> 00:43:29.223
So you're just living down here
by your wits.

398
00:43:29.348 --> 00:43:31.809
all on your own. no responsibilities.

399
00:43:31.934 --> 00:43:35.521
Not a one. It's incredible.
No dependents. no limits.

400
00:43:36.189 --> 00:43:38.649
It's the greatest life
a single guy could have.

401
00:43:38.774 --> 00:43:41.569
Hear that? This is my kind of place.

402
00:43:41.694 --> 00:43:42.820
Hello?

403
00:43:42.945 --> 00:43:44.655
Yeah... No. look. I can't talk right now.

404
00:43:44.780 --> 00:43:46.949
Yeah. No. I'm trying to recover
a dead sloth.

405
00:43:47.074 --> 00:43:48.117
Yeah.

406
00:43:50.286 --> 00:43:51.829
No. they're following me!

407
00:43:51.954 --> 00:43:54.165
I know! They think I'm crazy.

408
00:43:54.749 --> 00:43:57.001
No... Okay. we're going
into the Chasm of Death.

409
00:43:57.126 --> 00:43:58.920
I'm... I'm going to lose you.

410
00:43:59.045 --> 00:44:00.213
Yeah. I love you. too.

411
00:44:00.338 --> 00:44:02.798
All right. good-bye. Good-bye! Good-bye.

412
00:44:02.924 --> 00:44:04.508
Okay! Follow me.

413
00:44:05.051 --> 00:44:07.135
That's you in three weeks.

414
00:44:25.237 --> 00:44:28.114
So. why do they call it
the Chasm of Death?

415
00:44:28.532 --> 00:44:32.869
Well. we tried "Big Smelly Crack."
but that just made everybody giggle.

416
00:44:33.537 --> 00:44:35.163
Well. now what?

417
00:44:38.291 --> 00:44:39.543
Madame.

418
00:44:40.752 --> 00:44:42.212
She is not doing that!

419
00:44:43.588 --> 00:44:45.340
Rule number one.

420
00:44:48.843 --> 00:44:52.138
Come on. mammoth!
You're supposed to have a good memory.

421
00:44:52.264 --> 00:44:54.224
Always listen to Buck.

422
00:44:58.937 --> 00:45:02.732
Now. eyes forward. back straight. and...

423
00:45:02.858 --> 00:45:05.402
Oh. yes. breathe in the toxic fumes
and you'll probably die.

424
00:45:05.527 --> 00:45:06.611
Toxic fumes?

425
00:45:06.736 --> 00:45:10.240
- Just another day in paradise.
- Wait!

426
00:45:11.408 --> 00:45:13.410
Geronimo!

427
00:45:23.628 --> 00:45:26.798
- Ellie. you okay?
- You have to try this!

428
00:45:26.923 --> 00:45:30.552
All right. now pile on. everyone!
Couldn't be easier!

429
00:45:35.473 --> 00:45:36.892
Don't panic!

430
00:45:37.017 --> 00:45:39.561
Just some technical difficulties.

431
00:45:40.312 --> 00:45:42.314
Keep holding it in. boys!

432
00:45:45.817 --> 00:45:47.485
I can't take it anymore!

433
00:45:47.611 --> 00:45:49.237
He breathed it!

434
00:45:49.362 --> 00:45:51.281
And now I'm breathing it!

435
00:45:54.326 --> 00:45:56.452
Hey! We're not dead!

436
00:45:56.577 --> 00:45:58.078
You sound ridiculous!

437
00:45:58.204 --> 00:46:00.372
Me? You should hear you!

438
00:46:04.418 --> 00:46:07.296
All right. all right. And a one. and a two...

439
00:46:07.421 --> 00:46:09.965
Christmas. Christmas time is here

440
00:46:10.090 --> 00:46:12.134
Stop! Are you crazy?

441
00:46:14.512 --> 00:46:15.638
It's not poison.

442
00:46:22.353 --> 00:46:24.355
That is so disturbing!

443
00:46:26.774 --> 00:46:28.984
Stop laughing! All of you!

444
00:46:29.527 --> 00:46:31.820
"Stop laughing. all of you!"

445
00:46:34.365 --> 00:46:36.575
"What's rule number one?"

446
00:46:40.037 --> 00:46:42.331
They're just laughing.
What's so bad about that?

447
00:46:42.456 --> 00:46:44.375
They died laughing!

448
00:46:47.795 --> 00:46:49.255
Stop laughing!

449
00:46:49.713 --> 00:46:51.549
You know what's funny. though?

450
00:46:51.674 --> 00:46:54.009
We're trying to save Sid.

451
00:46:54.134 --> 00:46:56.262
and now we're all gonna die!

452
00:46:57.930 --> 00:47:01.600
- And I don't even like Sid!
- Who does? He's an idiot!

453
00:47:04.395 --> 00:47:08.190
Thanks for getting me into this mess.
It's the most fun I've had in years!

454
00:47:08.315 --> 00:47:12.444
Thank you for deserting the herd!
That was totally super!

455
00:47:19.618 --> 00:47:21.161
Stop that!

456
00:47:21.579 --> 00:47:24.290
Don't you see? We're all gonna die!

457
00:47:29.920 --> 00:47:32.047
We gotta do everything. huh?

458
00:47:39.096 --> 00:47:41.348
Sometimes I wet my bed!

459
00:47:41.473 --> 00:47:44.392
That's all right!
Sometimes I wet your bed!

460
00:47:56.946 --> 00:47:59.407
I'm not sure how much of that
you could hear.

461
00:47:59.532 --> 00:48:02.535
- I heard all of it.
- Right. Yeah.

462
00:48:03.036 --> 00:48:05.997
- You wet my bed?
- That was gas talk. dude.

463
00:48:06.748 --> 00:48:09.375
Well. better get moving.

464
00:48:09.500 --> 00:48:11.377
Aren't we forgetting something?

465
00:48:11.502 --> 00:48:13.755
Here. Rudy. Rudy. Rudy!

466
00:48:15.173 --> 00:48:16.841
I'm so lonely.

467
00:48:35.068 --> 00:48:37.153
Okay. Here you go. guys.

468
00:48:45.453 --> 00:48:47.455
What? You're not gonna
eat your vegetables?

469
00:48:47.580 --> 00:48:51.376
How are you gonna become
big. strong dinosaurs?

470
00:48:55.838 --> 00:49:00.593
No. I've raised them vegetarian.
It's a healthier lifestyle.

471
00:49:00.718 --> 00:49:04.222
I mean. look at me.
I have the pelt of a much younger sloth.

472
00:49:05.348 --> 00:49:08.977
Excuse me!
I'm trying to have a conversation here.

473
00:49:15.483 --> 00:49:17.861
No. no. no. That's not for us. kids.

474
00:49:17.986 --> 00:49:20.738
It's way too feathery and fleshy and...

475
00:49:21.656 --> 00:49:23.116
And alive!

476
00:49:30.540 --> 00:49:35.252
No! No. no. we do not eat
live animals. period!

477
00:49:36.086 --> 00:49:38.005
Now. go! Fly!

478
00:49:38.130 --> 00:49:39.715
Be free.

479
00:49:41.800 --> 00:49:44.094
little flightless bird.

480
00:49:46.763 --> 00:49:48.015
My bad.

481
00:49:48.891 --> 00:49:50.976
Hey. where are you going?

482
00:49:51.101 --> 00:49:53.270
This is how you resolve conflict?

483
00:49:53.395 --> 00:49:55.397
No wonder you're single!

484
00:49:59.776 --> 00:50:02.029
Come on. Am I talking to myself here?

485
00:50:02.154 --> 00:50:04.698
I say. "They're vegetarian."
You say. "Grrr."

486
00:50:04.823 --> 00:50:07.284
I say. "Can we talk about talk this?"
You say. "Grrr."

487
00:50:07.409 --> 00:50:09.620
I don't call that communication.

488
00:50:09.745 --> 00:50:12.456
See? That's your answer to everything.

489
00:50:25.302 --> 00:50:28.263
What are you afraid of?
You're the biggest thing on Earth!

490
00:50:32.643 --> 00:50:34.102
Aren't you?

491
00:50:37.564 --> 00:50:38.649
Hey!

492
00:50:47.115 --> 00:50:49.952
They'll never survive.
It's dangerous by day.

493
00:50:50.077 --> 00:50:51.828
But it's even worse at night.

494
00:50:51.954 --> 00:50:54.164
Plus. their guide is a lunatic.

495
00:50:54.289 --> 00:50:56.583
What? You mean. Buck? He's wacko!

496
00:50:56.708 --> 00:50:57.751
I am not!

497
00:50:57.876 --> 00:50:58.919
Totally bonkers.

498
00:50:59.044 --> 00:51:00.170
And his feet smell.

499
00:51:00.295 --> 00:51:01.588
Shut up! You shut up.

500
00:51:01.713 --> 00:51:03.382
Oh. you little...

501
00:51:03.507 --> 00:51:04.716
Gotcha!

502
00:51:05.008 --> 00:51:06.885
He's strangling his own foot.

503
00:51:07.010 --> 00:51:09.304
- Shouldn't we get moving?
- What?

504
00:51:09.513 --> 00:51:12.266
And give Rudy a midnight snack?
Not likely!

505
00:51:12.391 --> 00:51:14.309
The skull's right.
Take a load off. mammals.

506
00:51:14.434 --> 00:51:15.811
We'll camp here.

507
00:51:15.936 --> 00:51:17.396
Now. who's hungry?

508
00:51:17.521 --> 00:51:18.522
I am!

509
00:51:18.647 --> 00:51:20.858
You don't need the calories!

510
00:51:25.528 --> 00:51:30.241
There I was. my back against the wall.
no way out.

511
00:51:31.576 --> 00:51:34.620
perched on the razor's edge of oblivion.

512
00:51:34.996 --> 00:51:39.333
staring into the eye
of the Great White Beast.

513
00:52:41.229 --> 00:52:44.106
- Were you killed?
- Sadly. yes.

514
00:52:44.232 --> 00:52:45.358
But I lived!

515
00:52:48.569 --> 00:52:52.865
Never had I felt so alive
than when I was so close to death.

516
00:52:53.908 --> 00:52:56.202
Just before Rudy could suck me
down his gullet.

517
00:52:56.327 --> 00:52:58.412
I grabbed hold of that gross.
pink. fleshy thing

518
00:52:58.538 --> 00:53:00.331
that dangles at the back of the throat.

519
00:53:01.457 --> 00:53:04.877
I hung onto that sucker. and I swung
back and forth.

520
00:53:05.044 --> 00:53:09.882
and back and forth. and back and forth.
and back and forth. and back

521
00:53:11.049 --> 00:53:12.968
and forth. and back and forth.

522
00:53:13.093 --> 00:53:16.721
until finally. I let go
and I shot right out of his mouth!

523
00:53:18.431 --> 00:53:22.102
I may have lost an eye that day.
but I got this!

524
00:53:23.144 --> 00:53:25.313
- Rudy's tooth!
- Dang!

525
00:53:25.981 --> 00:53:28.275
It's like the old saying. "An eye for a tooth.

526
00:53:28.400 --> 00:53:31.570
"a nose for a chin. a butt for a..."

527
00:53:32.654 --> 00:53:35.532
Well. it's an old saying.
but it's not a very good one.

528
00:53:35.657 --> 00:53:38.785
- You are Super Weasel!
- Ultra-Weasel!

529
00:53:38.910 --> 00:53:40.453
Diesel Weasel!

530
00:53:45.292 --> 00:53:46.793
What? He is.

531
00:53:47.127 --> 00:53:50.046
Now let me tell you about the time
I used a sharpened clam shell

532
00:53:50.172 --> 00:53:52.591
to turn a T-Rex into a T-Rachel.

533
00:53:53.008 --> 00:53:54.426
- Yes. master.
- Yes. master.

534
00:53:55.302 --> 00:53:57.596
That's enough fairy tales for one night.

535
00:53:57.721 --> 00:54:00.265
Come on. Ellie. you should rest now.

536
00:54:01.224 --> 00:54:02.392
Life of the party.

537
00:54:02.517 --> 00:54:05.228
All right. you guys get some shut-eye.
I'll keep watch.

538
00:54:05.353 --> 00:54:09.733
Don't worry. Buck. We got this.
Night time is possum time.

539
00:54:09.858 --> 00:54:12.152
Yeah! We own the night. baby.

540
00:54:26.708 --> 00:54:28.376
Good night. Rudy.

541
00:54:40.764 --> 00:54:42.891
Wait. wait. What about me?

542
00:54:58.031 --> 00:55:01.116
Sleep well. kids!
We have a busy day tomorrow.

543
00:55:01.575 --> 00:55:03.577
Foraging. hunting.

544
00:55:05.704 --> 00:55:07.623
missing my friends.

545
00:55:08.165 --> 00:55:10.668
who probably aren't missing me.

546
00:55:24.890 --> 00:55:26.976
You're a real softie. you know that?

547
00:55:50.833 --> 00:55:51.959
Manny?

548
00:55:56.714 --> 00:55:59.466
Crash? Eddie?

549
00:56:03.512 --> 00:56:04.805
Manny?

550
00:56:23.616 --> 00:56:26.118
What's going on? Are you okay?

551
00:56:27.620 --> 00:56:30.164
I'm sorry. I just wanted to keep you safe.

552
00:56:30.289 --> 00:56:33.626
and now you're in the most dangerous
place in the world.

553
00:56:33.751 --> 00:56:36.045
Hey. This isn't your fault.

554
00:56:36.170 --> 00:56:39.507
It's bigger than both of us.
We have to get Sid.

555
00:56:40.132 --> 00:56:43.177
Yeah. but if I had been
a better friend to him.

556
00:56:43.636 --> 00:56:46.096
- we wouldn't be here.
- Better friend?

557
00:56:46.347 --> 00:56:48.516
Are you plucking my whiskers?

558
00:56:48.641 --> 00:56:52.852
You risked your life. your mate
and your baby to save your buddy.

559
00:56:54.145 --> 00:56:57.607
Not the best husband or father.
but a darn good friend!

560
00:57:05.198 --> 00:57:06.324
Hey!

561
00:58:16.895 --> 00:58:18.521
Everybody. stop!

562
00:58:20.273 --> 00:58:21.983
I smell something.

563
00:58:27.155 --> 00:58:29.991
It smells like a buzzard's butt fell off

564
00:58:30.742 --> 00:58:33.369
and then got sprayed on
by a bunch of skunks.

565
00:58:33.494 --> 00:58:34.621
That's Sid.

566
00:58:34.746 --> 00:58:38.040
Mammals. we have ourselves
a crime scene.

567
00:58:38.624 --> 00:58:41.793
A tuft of fur. Half-eaten carcass!

568
00:58:42.461 --> 00:58:44.838
Hunk of... No!

569
00:58:45.297 --> 00:58:46.590
Broccoli.

570
00:58:47.549 --> 00:58:48.717
Here's what I think happened.

571
00:58:49.218 --> 00:58:50.344
Dinosaur attacks Sid.

572
00:58:50.469 --> 00:58:54.264
Sid fights back with piece of broccoli.
leaving dinosaur

573
00:58:55.599 --> 00:58:56.725
a vegetable.

574
00:58:56.850 --> 00:58:59.978
Are you nuts? Sid's not violent.
Or coordinated.

575
00:59:00.354 --> 00:59:02.397
Yeah. And where's the dinosaur?

576
00:59:02.523 --> 00:59:04.858
All right. All right. good point.

577
00:59:04.983 --> 00:59:06.193
Theory two.

578
00:59:06.318 --> 00:59:07.528
Sid's eating broccoli.

579
00:59:07.653 --> 00:59:08.946
dinosaur eats Sid.

580
00:59:09.071 --> 00:59:11.823
dinosaur steps on broccoli.
leaving broccoli

581
00:59:12.574 --> 00:59:13.825
a vegetable.

582
00:59:13.951 --> 00:59:16.203
Buck. when exactly
did you lose your mind?

583
00:59:17.079 --> 00:59:18.080
Three months ago.

584
00:59:18.205 --> 00:59:20.874
I woke up one morning
married to a pineapple.

585
00:59:20.999 --> 00:59:22.209
An ugly pineapple.

586
00:59:24.211 --> 00:59:25.546
But I loved her.

587
00:59:25.671 --> 00:59:28.882
Buck. I think you missed
a little clue over here.

588
00:59:30.259 --> 00:59:33.929
Well. your friend might be alive.
but not for long.

589
00:59:35.556 --> 00:59:37.224
Rudy's closing in.

590
00:59:38.267 --> 00:59:39.309
- Whoa!
- Whoa!

591
00:59:39.434 --> 00:59:42.896
You got it. The Plates of Woe.

592
00:59:43.355 --> 00:59:45.065
Or whatever's left of them.

593
01:00:54.800 --> 01:00:57.929
Single file. everyone! Head for Lava Falls.

594
01:01:11.567 --> 01:01:15.696
- What's that sound?
- It's the wind. It's speaking to us.

595
01:01:16.322 --> 01:01:18.491
- What's it saying?
- I don't know.

596
01:01:18.616 --> 01:01:20.076
I don't speak Wind.

597
01:01:29.126 --> 01:01:32.463
- Ellie!
- I'm fine. Don't worry about me.

598
01:01:32.588 --> 01:01:34.173
I'm just taking my...

599
01:01:37.093 --> 01:01:38.219
Ellie!

600
01:01:40.930 --> 01:01:43.015
- Manny!
- Get to the ledge!

601
01:01:59.949 --> 01:02:01.158
Ellie!

602
01:02:02.618 --> 01:02:04.412
Ellie! Where are you?

603
01:02:04.745 --> 01:02:07.123
It's okay! I'm up here!

604
01:02:07.498 --> 01:02:10.251
Hang on. Ellie! We'll be right there!

605
01:02:32.606 --> 01:02:34.816
Wait! Sloth down!

606
01:02:37.068 --> 01:02:39.654
Wait. Wait. Time out!

607
01:02:40.572 --> 01:02:44.451
Hold up. You guys are getting fast!

608
01:02:48.872 --> 01:02:52.751
It's not so bad down here.
Nice weather. friendly neighbors.

609
01:02:59.966 --> 01:03:01.468
Hi. neighbor.

610
01:03:04.804 --> 01:03:06.556
- Rudy.
- Rudy?

611
01:03:08.475 --> 01:03:11.102
- Never heard that kind of dino before.
- That's Sid!

612
01:03:11.561 --> 01:03:14.940
- We'll have to move fast.
- Manny! Pineapples!

613
01:03:15.482 --> 01:03:17.609
- Pineapples?
- She gets cravings.

614
01:03:17.734 --> 01:03:20.946
Pomegranates? Grapefruits! Nectarines?

615
01:03:21.071 --> 01:03:22.822
She's ordering a fruit cocktail.

616
01:03:22.989 --> 01:03:24.616
Come on. think!

617
01:03:25.575 --> 01:03:26.910
Peaches!

618
01:03:27.786 --> 01:03:29.079
Peaches?

619
01:03:29.746 --> 01:03:32.666
Peaches! The baby! What. now?

620
01:03:32.791 --> 01:03:34.584
This? Not good.

621
01:03:34.709 --> 01:03:36.086
The baby's coming!
Did you guys hear that?

622
01:03:36.211 --> 01:03:37.754
'Cause sometimes
I imagine it in my head. but...

623
01:03:37.879 --> 01:03:39.548
Can you try to hold it in?

624
01:03:39.673 --> 01:03:41.716
Can somebody slap him for me?

625
01:03:42.676 --> 01:03:44.135
Done and done.

626
01:03:44.511 --> 01:03:46.137
Just sit tight. We're coming!

627
01:03:46.263 --> 01:03:48.765
There's only one thing to do.
Possums. you're with me.

628
01:03:48.890 --> 01:03:51.184
Manny. you take care of Ellie
until we get back.

629
01:03:51.309 --> 01:03:52.936
What? No. you can't leave now!

630
01:03:53.061 --> 01:03:55.397
She's off the trail!
What about rule number two?

631
01:03:55.522 --> 01:03:58.066
Rule number five says
you can ignore rule number two

632
01:03:58.191 --> 01:04:01.403
if there's a female involved.
or possibly a cute dog.

633
01:04:01.528 --> 01:04:03.446
You know I just make up these rules
as I go along.

634
01:04:03.572 --> 01:04:07.449
- Yeah. but. but she's... You have to...
- Manny. it's all right.

635
01:04:08.117 --> 01:04:09.785
I got your back.

636
01:04:11.495 --> 01:04:14.165
Now you're talking! Come on. lads.

637
01:04:16.792 --> 01:04:20.754
- Take care of our sister. mister.
- No pressure.

638
01:04:21.463 --> 01:04:23.132
What does that mean. "I got your back"?

639
01:04:23.257 --> 01:04:24.675
I mean. I'd rather they covered the front.

640
01:04:24.800 --> 01:04:26.343
That's where all the good stuff is. isn't it?

641
01:04:26.468 --> 01:04:28.137
We gotta move.

642
01:04:32.808 --> 01:04:35.102
Okay. All right. It's okay.

643
01:04:35.978 --> 01:04:38.105
Daddy's... Daddy's coming.

644
01:04:38.731 --> 01:04:41.775
I gotta say. sweetheart.
you really got timing.

645
01:05:02.171 --> 01:05:06.509
Go away! Go away!
Stranger danger! Stranger danger!

646
01:05:19.188 --> 01:05:21.774
Don't worry. It's just lava.

647
01:05:22.942 --> 01:05:25.569
Deadly boiling lava!

648
01:05:41.293 --> 01:05:44.421
- Boys. are you ready for adventure?
- Yes. sir!

649
01:05:44.547 --> 01:05:46.423
- For danger?
- Yes. sir!

650
01:05:46.549 --> 01:05:47.925
For death?

651
01:05:48.634 --> 01:05:49.885
Can you repeat the question?

652
01:05:50.010 --> 01:05:51.262
Jump!

653
01:06:02.105 --> 01:06:02.689
That's right! Come on!

654
01:06:02.689 --> 01:06:04.107
That's right! Come on!

655
01:06:06.860 --> 01:06:08.611
Have you ever flown one of these before?

656
01:06:08.736 --> 01:06:10.822
No! First time. actually.

657
01:06:19.038 --> 01:06:21.124
- There she is!
- Ellie!

658
01:06:21.249 --> 01:06:22.458
Manny!

659
01:06:27.130 --> 01:06:28.464
I need to get to her!

660
01:06:28.590 --> 01:06:30.466
Listen. I'll protect Ellie.

661
01:06:30.592 --> 01:06:32.135
- You stop those guys.
- But...

662
01:06:32.260 --> 01:06:36.514
Manny. if they reach her. it'll be too late.
You have to trust me.

663
01:06:40.185 --> 01:06:42.145
All right. Let's do it.

664
01:07:18.640 --> 01:07:21.226
My paws are burning. baby!
They're burning!

665
01:07:21.351 --> 01:07:23.353
I got to tip-toe.
Tippy-toe. Tippy-toe.

666
01:07:23.478 --> 01:07:26.648
Excuse me. twinkle toes!
Giving birth here.

667
01:07:27.106 --> 01:07:30.026
Right. Sorry. You okay?

668
01:07:30.276 --> 01:07:33.530
Am I okay?
Do you know anything about childbirth?

669
01:07:33.655 --> 01:07:35.990
No. not really. but Manny's coming.

670
01:07:43.580 --> 01:07:46.792
Diego. I'm scared. Can I hold your paw?

671
01:07:46.917 --> 01:07:48.877
Yeah. of course.

672
01:07:49.002 --> 01:07:50.838
Just go with the pain.

673
01:07:52.089 --> 01:07:54.341
- It's just a contraction.
- No!

674
01:08:07.187 --> 01:08:09.064
Look! He's right there!

675
01:08:09.189 --> 01:08:11.191
- Roger!
- No! Sid!

676
01:08:11.316 --> 01:08:12.818
I know! Roger!

677
01:08:12.943 --> 01:08:15.779
How about we get Sid first
and then go back for Roger?

678
01:08:16.530 --> 01:08:17.656
Never mind!

679
01:08:29.793 --> 01:08:31.086
Buck?

680
01:08:46.894 --> 01:08:50.522
No. no. Buck! Buck. wait! Sid's that way!

681
01:08:50.647 --> 01:08:52.441
Tell that to them!

682
01:08:54.234 --> 01:08:56.987
Bring it on. you chicken-headed freaks!

683
01:09:14.755 --> 01:09:17.716
Don't worry about a thing.
You're doing fine.

684
01:09:19.176 --> 01:09:20.844
It's going great.

685
01:09:21.678 --> 01:09:22.971
Excuse me.

686
01:09:26.058 --> 01:09:27.809
Just keep breathing!

687
01:09:28.143 --> 01:09:29.228
Diego!

688
01:09:29.353 --> 01:09:32.146
Just breathe! That's the important thing.

689
01:09:40.238 --> 01:09:41.864
Grab that ammo!

690
01:09:45.785 --> 01:09:47.745
Bogey. three o'clock! Fire!

691
01:09:56.462 --> 01:09:59.507
This is awesome!

692
01:10:02.885 --> 01:10:04.345
Light it up!

693
01:10:05.555 --> 01:10:07.682
- Yeah!
- Hasta la vista. birdy!

694
01:10:20.153 --> 01:10:21.946
Let's get our sloth!

695
01:10:22.071 --> 01:10:25.199
We're hit! We're hit! Mayday! Mayday!

696
01:10:25.324 --> 01:10:28.911
We're losing altitude! Hold these!

697
01:10:32.039 --> 01:10:33.624
Tastes like fish.

698
01:10:33.749 --> 01:10:35.877
Okay. That's just weird.

699
01:10:37.545 --> 01:10:40.464
- I love you. bro!
- I know!

700
01:10:41.174 --> 01:10:43.176
Snap out of it! Come on!

701
01:10:44.051 --> 01:10:45.261
Pull!

702
01:10:54.061 --> 01:10:57.690
This is the end of Sid the Sloth!

703
01:11:05.239 --> 01:11:07.492
- Help!
- No. Sid! It's me!

704
01:11:07.617 --> 01:11:09.368
- And me!
- And me!

705
01:11:09.494 --> 01:11:12.538
I don't want to panic anybody.
but who's flying this thing?

706
01:11:12.663 --> 01:11:13.664
Oops!

707
01:11:26.593 --> 01:11:28.678
No. no. wait! Wait! My kids!

708
01:11:32.098 --> 01:11:34.559
I never even got to say good-bye.

709
01:11:37.979 --> 01:11:40.690
You can do it! Push! Push!

710
01:11:40.815 --> 01:11:42.359
I can't do it!

711
01:11:42.484 --> 01:11:44.319
Just one more big push!

712
01:11:44.444 --> 01:11:47.239
You have no idea what I'm going through!

713
01:11:47.781 --> 01:11:50.909
Okay. forget I said that.
Let's do this together.

714
01:12:01.127 --> 01:12:03.630
I liked you guys better
when you were extinct.

715
01:12:09.010 --> 01:12:10.262
Getting dizzy.

716
01:12:12.055 --> 01:12:15.934
Manny! Come on. buddy.
I think we're getting close.

717
01:12:51.178 --> 01:12:52.804
She's perfect.

718
01:12:53.847 --> 01:12:56.600
I think we should call her Ellie.

719
01:12:58.518 --> 01:12:59.853
Little Ellie.

720
01:12:59.978 --> 01:13:02.230
I got a better name. Peaches.

721
01:13:03.190 --> 01:13:04.524
Peaches?

722
01:13:04.649 --> 01:13:09.612
Why not? She's sweet and round
and covered with fuzz.

723
01:13:10.321 --> 01:13:11.614
Peaches.

724
01:13:12.490 --> 01:13:13.782
I love it.

725
01:13:17.328 --> 01:13:18.746
I saw that. tough guy.

726
01:13:18.871 --> 01:13:22.082
No. no. That last dino
caught my eye with a claw. and...

727
01:13:22.833 --> 01:13:24.585
All right. so I'm not made of stone.

728
01:13:24.710 --> 01:13:26.295
Incoming!

729
01:13:28.172 --> 01:13:29.507
It's Sid!

730
01:13:34.470 --> 01:13:36.847
- It's a boy!
- That's its tail.

731
01:13:36.972 --> 01:13:38.349
It's a girl!

732
01:13:39.350 --> 01:13:43.854
Hi. sweetheart. Hello. hello!
It's Uncle Sid. Yes. it is.

733
01:13:43.979 --> 01:13:48.192
You're so beautiful. She is!
She looks just like her mother.

734
01:13:48.901 --> 01:13:50.402
Thank goodness.

735
01:13:50.820 --> 01:13:54.406
No offense. Manny! No offense.
You're beautiful on the inside!

736
01:13:54.532 --> 01:13:56.242
It's good to have you back. Sid.

737
01:13:56.367 --> 01:13:59.995
Never thought I would say this.
but I missed you. buddy.

738
01:14:04.416 --> 01:14:06.710
Now I wish my kids were here.

739
01:14:07.086 --> 01:14:09.255
You could have been friends.

740
01:14:10.464 --> 01:14:11.590
Ellie!

741
01:14:15.427 --> 01:14:17.805
I promised myself I wouldn't cry.

742
01:14:17.930 --> 01:14:19.139
I didn't.

743
01:14:24.728 --> 01:14:27.606
I forgot what it was like
to be part of a family.

744
01:14:27.731 --> 01:14:30.276
What about you?
Ever thought about having kids?

745
01:14:34.071 --> 01:14:36.949
All right. mammals. let's get you home.

746
01:16:04.035 --> 01:16:07.539
This is it. mammals.
Right where you started.

747
01:16:07.664 --> 01:16:10.917
This was fun!
We could make it a regular thing.

748
01:16:12.043 --> 01:16:13.545
I don't know about that.

749
01:16:13.670 --> 01:16:18.007
Right! Right. Yes. because of
all the mortal peril. of course.

750
01:16:19.259 --> 01:16:21.302
Well. the Buck stops here.

751
01:16:22.512 --> 01:16:24.389
We couldn't have done it without you.

752
01:16:24.514 --> 01:16:27.517
Well. obviously. But good times. just the...

753
01:16:29.143 --> 01:16:31.187
We're not alone. are we?

754
01:16:35.525 --> 01:16:36.860
Hello. Rudy.

755
01:16:45.994 --> 01:16:47.202
Run!

756
01:16:54.293 --> 01:16:56.753
Over here. you colossal fossil!

757
01:16:57.254 --> 01:16:59.214
Looking for something?

758
01:17:00.883 --> 01:17:02.593
Why don't you come and get it!

759
01:17:02.718 --> 01:17:04.428
To the cave! Go!

760
01:17:07.848 --> 01:17:10.642
- Stay with the baby.
- We'll be fine. Go.

761
01:17:18.275 --> 01:17:19.485
Wuss.

762
01:17:32.039 --> 01:17:33.832
Pop goes the weasel!

763
01:17:46.136 --> 01:17:47.804
Come on! Move!

764
01:17:50.390 --> 01:17:53.435
- Diego! Catch!
- Got it!

765
01:18:03.487 --> 01:18:06.031
Through the hole. over the valley.
One more loop...

766
01:18:06.740 --> 01:18:08.617
Come on. lads! Heave!

767
01:18:23.674 --> 01:18:25.634
Better luck next time. snowflake.

768
01:18:25.759 --> 01:18:27.886
This isn't going to hold him long! Let's go!

769
01:18:28.011 --> 01:18:29.638
Hold up. guys!

770
01:18:52.201 --> 01:18:54.162
Way to go. Momzilla!

771
01:19:26.235 --> 01:19:28.988
Come here. kids.
Well. let me tell you something.

772
01:19:29.113 --> 01:19:31.032
You're where you belong now.

773
01:19:31.157 --> 01:19:35.244
And I'm sure you're going to grow up
to be giant. horrifying dinosaurs

774
01:19:36.370 --> 01:19:37.705
just like your mother.

775
01:19:40.500 --> 01:19:41.876
And Momma.

776
01:19:43.044 --> 01:19:45.338
take good care of our kids.

777
01:20:13.533 --> 01:20:16.619
- You were a good parent. Sid.
- Thanks.

778
01:20:17.578 --> 01:20:19.455
- Can I baby-sit for you?
- Not a chance.

779
01:20:19.580 --> 01:20:22.875
- Come on. I work cheap!
- All right. I'll think about it.

780
01:20:23.960 --> 01:20:25.168
Yes!

781
01:20:25.293 --> 01:20:26.753
Never happen.

782
01:20:30.674 --> 01:20:33.802
He's gone. What am I supposed to do now?

783
01:20:34.219 --> 01:20:36.847
That's easy. Come with us.

784
01:20:38.265 --> 01:20:40.267
You mean up there?

785
01:20:42.435 --> 01:20:44.312
I never thought of going back.

786
01:20:44.437 --> 01:20:47.649
I've been down here so long.
it feels like up to me.

787
01:20:47.774 --> 01:20:49.860
I'm not sure I can fit in up there anymore.

788
01:20:49.985 --> 01:20:53.947
So? Look at us.
We look like a normal herd to you?

789
01:21:23.310 --> 01:21:24.936
So long. big guy.

790
01:21:36.740 --> 01:21:39.201
That's our cue! Come on. Peaches.

791
01:21:40.744 --> 01:21:42.162
He's alive!

792
01:21:43.830 --> 01:21:45.040
Buck?

793
01:21:46.333 --> 01:21:48.126
I... I got to...

794
01:21:49.419 --> 01:21:50.504
Yeah.

795
01:21:50.754 --> 01:21:54.174
Besides. this world should
really stay down here.

796
01:21:56.092 --> 01:21:58.094
Take care of them. Tiger.

797
01:21:58.345 --> 01:22:00.347
"Always listen to Buck."

798
01:22:01.264 --> 01:22:03.058
We're almost out!

799
01:22:09.898 --> 01:22:11.191
Rudy!

800
01:22:33.087 --> 01:22:34.797
Is everybody okay?

801
01:22:35.339 --> 01:22:36.882
Where's Buck?

802
01:22:39.510 --> 01:22:42.596
Don't worry. He's where he wants to be.

803
01:22:43.931 --> 01:22:46.725
- Is he gonna be okay?
- Are you kidding?

804
01:22:46.851 --> 01:22:50.729
Nothing could kill that weasel.
It's Rudy I'm worried about.

805
01:23:02.074 --> 01:23:05.327
I know this "baby makes three" thing
isn't for you.

806
01:23:05.452 --> 01:23:08.622
but whatever you decide to do...

807
01:23:08.747 --> 01:23:10.499
I'm not leaving. buddy.

808
01:23:10.624 --> 01:23:13.127
Life of adventure? It's right here.

809
01:23:13.544 --> 01:23:17.047
But I got a whole speech here.
I've been working on it.

810
01:23:17.173 --> 01:23:20.593
How can I show you
that I'm strong and sensitive?

811
01:23:20.718 --> 01:23:22.344
Noble yet caring?

812
01:23:24.513 --> 01:23:25.723
Thanks.

813
01:23:40.779 --> 01:23:42.740
They grow so fast. huh?

814
01:23:42.865 --> 01:23:44.492
Yeah. I mean. look at my kids.

815
01:23:44.617 --> 01:23:47.328
Seems like they were born one day
and then gone the next.

816
01:23:47.453 --> 01:23:48.954
They were. Sid.

817
01:23:49.079 --> 01:23:51.415
Yeah. That was a lot of work.

818
01:24:03.301 --> 01:24:06.846
That's right. sweetheart.
Welcome to the Ice Age.

819
01:34:00.643 --> 01:34:01.644
English - US

820
01:34:02.305 --> 01:35:02.294
Do you want subtitles for any video?
